<title type="html"><![CDATA[What's this NES game?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=1166&amp;p=10161#p10161"><![CDATA[
I remember Metal Storm fondly.  It had such potential, in terms of graphics and gameplay.   The game even had a spread in Nintendo Power, touting its unique gameplay.  Most notably, the parallax background scrolling and "switchable" gravity were way out there for the time.<br /><br />But its execution was strangely lackluster, it had garish palettes, so-so music and the stages were quite repetitive.  Also, some of the later stages were heavily twitch-based, which leads to some extreme frustration given you have limited lives and continues.<br /><br />I would have loved to see this game redone as a more shooter-style SNES game.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=273">pragma</a> — Mon Feb 27, 2006 7:59 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
