A long time ago, I played some NES game that I absolutely CANNOT remember the name of, so I'll describe it here, hopefully someone knows what it is.<br /><br />It was some kind of platformer which you probably could shoot in too. The main character was a robot or something. The character's sprite was larger than what normally appears in NES games, so it was a large robot sprite. I know I'm being vague, but that's all I can remember. I think one of the levels had a weird vertical looping thing that Sonic does sometimes. It's NOT Megaman. <img src="http://forums.nesdev.com/images/smilies/icon_razz.gif" alt=":P" title="Razz" /><br /><br />Does anyone know?<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=21">Drag</a> — Sat Feb 25, 2006 11:29 pm</p><hr />
